<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para><db:link xlink:href="qpropertychangehandler.xml">QPropertyChangeHandler</db:link>&lt;Functor&gt; is created when registering a callback on a <db:link xlink:href="qproperty.xml">QProperty</db:link> to listen to changes to the property's value, using <db:link xlink:href="qproperty.xml#onValueChanged">QProperty::onValueChanged</db:link> and <db:link xlink:href="qproperty.xml#subscribe">QProperty::subscribe</db:link>. As long as the change handler is alive, the callback remains installed.</db:para>
<db:para>A handler instance can be transferred between C++ scopes using move semantics.</db:para>
</db:section>
